Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: 10:05 AM Defendant Takye Malik Wade-Jackson does not appear in Court, Atty Liesl E. Nelson, ADA Joseph M. Schieffer appears for the State of Wisconsin. Atty Nelson states DE did leave a message last week that he was having problems getting a ride. ADA Schieffer is requesting a warrant but to Stay until Thursday at 4:00 pm. Court will authorize warrant Statewide and stay until 4:00 pm Thursday June 2nd. Court adjourned at 10:06 am.
Status conference on May 31, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Information filed with the Court.  DE waives further reading of the Information. NG.  Bond remains in its present form. Court adjourned at 4:16 pm.

4:02 PM Defendant Takye Malik Wade-Jackson appears in Court, Atty Liesl E. Nelson, ADA Joseph M. Schieffer appears for the State of Wisconsin.. Officer Jordan Hemker. S/T. Atty Schieffer questions Officer. Court reflects identification of DE. Cross Atty Nelson. ADA Schieffer is requesting the Court find probable cause and bind DE over, Atty Nelson argues.  The Court finds probable cause a felony was committed and binds DE over for further proceedings.  Status conference scheduled for May 31, 2022 at 10:00 am.
